line_1: Begin We in our Children's Reading.
line_2: I mention'd diff'rent Ways of Breeding:

line_1: With a Turn, at least no Aversion, to Reading:
line_2: Chuse a Woman of Wisdom, as well as good Breeding,

line_1: And laugh'd at pedantry and reading.
Who taught me betimes to love Working and Reading.
line_2: But Thanks to my Friends for their Care in my Breeding,

line_1: Had learnt, with very moderate reading,
line_2: The whole new system of good breeding:

line_1: Think him not ignorant of reading;
line_2: Yet tho' so polish'd FLORIO'S breeding,

line_1: He was a prodigy of reading.
line_2: At least, with men of FLORIO'S breeding,

line_1: Her native sense improv'd by reading,

line_2: His tea grew cold, whilst he, unheeding,

line_1: Tho', had they but a little Reading,
line_2: Ovid would teach them better Breeding.

line_1: And I, a fool, with too much reading,
line_2: But You, a slave to too much breeding,
